00:23:56,123 --> 00:23:57,371
He was a convicted felon.

358
00:23:58,798 --> 00:24:00,035
Could angel maker be
a vigilante?

359
00:24:00,103 --> 00:24:04,839
Well, vigilantes are
pragmatic, they're purposeful;

360
00:24:04,908 --> 00:24:08,377
They don't lay down and sleep
under their crimes.

361
00:24:10,380 --> 00:24:14,582
In his mind, he was doing God's work.
That spells vigilante.

362
00:24:14,650 --> 00:24:18,085
Well, playing at God has
other advantages. One of them...

363
00:24:18,153 --> 00:24:21,989
Is always being alone. So he
makes angels out of demons.

364
00:24:22,057 --> 00:24:23,892
How does he know
they're demons?

365
00:24:23,959 --> 00:24:26,560
He doesn't have to know.

366
00:24:26,628 --> 00:24:28,995
All he has to do is believe.

367
00:24:34,602 --> 00:24:37,471
Has Jack begun to suspect?

368
00:24:37,539 --> 00:24:39,807
He's a behavioral specialist.
He must know

369
00:24:39,874 --> 00:24:41,809
you are keeping something
from him.

370
00:24:41,876 --> 00:24:46,546
Oh, he knows. He asked me
if I was having an affair...

371
00:24:46,613 --> 00:24:49,849
by reassuring me
that he didn't have to ask.

372
00:24:49,917 --> 00:24:52,485
I doubt he believes
you're unfaithful.

373
00:24:52,553 --> 00:24:54,420
And why do you doubt that?

374
00:24:54,488 --> 00:24:57,356
It's clear you love
your husband.

375
00:24:57,424 --> 00:25:01,726
